// ReceiveEvents reads from the partition using a bounded per-call timeout so
// low-volume streams are dispatched promptly. azeventhubs.ReceiveEvents blocks
// until either count events arrive or the context is done; without a bound it
// would stall until a full batch of count events accumulated. On our timeout it
// returns whatever events were received so far (possibly none) with no error.
